value.0: Karrav Maubar is a well known member of anchorhead and a well respected merchant. She sells everything that you can think of and will buy almost anything, should she be able to make a profit. Only problem with Karrav is that she hates being screwed around. If someone screws her over, sometimes they are never seen again. Perhaps it's best to stay on her good side, right?

Nipp Pinul is an ordinary Jawa. He sells things and buys things. The only thing about this Jawa is that his clothing is just the slightest tinge of a darker brown. He will usually buy and sell things that you want or don't need. Just don't get your fingers to close, he's known for biting.

MR-03478 is not your typical droid. Once a well known bounty, he suffered and unfortunate accident of falling into a crevice deep in the desert. Within the crevice was a pool of water in which MR could not escape. One he was found, his arms and legs were already rusted and now they are locked in a permanent position. Since this was his new fate, he moved into Anchorhead and is now a merchant. Noone really buys from him, since he can't actually move to buy yhings or sell things.

M.O.A (or Merchants of Anchorhead) are an association that was created by all the merchants within Anchorhead. This group is the deciding factor of who or what can trade in Anchorhead as a merchant. As M.O.A grew, they decided they needed to hire guards. The M.O.A Guard's are respected mercenaries or bounty hunters that have decided to slow down and become a guard. They aren't to be messed with and all have different stories / history.

Anchor Aye and Anchor Bee are identical twins that take pleasure in annoying and confusing anyone that meets them. On top of this, they are a few brain cells short of an actual conversation and tend to talk through one another and finish each others sentences. This can cause anyone to become irritated quite quickly, but they don't seem to mind. They just laugh it off and carry on with annoying one another.

Coopemma Lakeanso was once a famous child-hood actor, who lost hist fortune to his addiction to death sticks. He lives his life on the streets of Anchorhead begging for spare credits to fuel his addiction. On the surface he looks like a lowley beggar, with missing teeth and peeling skin, but he is actually a very intelligent and attractive man. Perhaps he just needs a good bath?

Kastod Candut is probably the strangest merchant in Anchorhead. He is a selkath, whom usually spend their time in the water. He has been travelling the world for a very long time and has stopped on Tatooine. His chest plate is always pulsing mist onto his skin to keep it moist and allowing him to live on Tatooine for as long as he needs. He's a very secrative individual and will usually only trade me those he trusts.

Ku'klez Nahiwo is a travelling merchant who has stopped in Anchorhead to refuel his ship and restock his supplies. Not looking at selling anything, he just seems to stick to himself and gives every passer by a single nod. Nothing special is notable about Ku'klez, other than a few scars that round down both of his arms.

Slimmat Grar was once a slave trader. Buying and selling children and woman to everyone that was interested in doing so. Eventually, he discovered this wasn't good money (and was highly illegal) so he moved from that and transferred to selling speeder bikes. Unfortunately for him, all the speeder bikes he sells are either stolen or broken. He is quite old, which means his memory is slowly deteriorating. Every now and then, he thinks he recognizes one of the children he sold.

Triger Stigle is a mysterious robed female. She stares at you from a distance and those eyes follow you everywhere you go. As you approach, the smell of roses covers you. The smell is very alluring the closer you get. Her whole aura seems welcoming and the rumours of the town seem to be that she uses that to her advantage. The town guards avoid her like the plague and tend to just leave her to do what she wishes.

Sizzla is the sister of Booma. Although she looks like a threat, she is quite sweet and approachable. She's the brains of the operation and is usually found ensuring Booma doesn't blow himself up or someone else. She doesn't seem to dress appropriately for the weather or where she is, but she doesn't care. She keeps to herself mostly and was only doing what she was to ensure that her brother didn't get herself killed.
